      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">The ports <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A, B)</b> on the secondary Modbus devices connects
to the connector <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(C)</b> on the Ethernet patch panel with a shielded
cable.</p>
         <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">Do not change the default wiring
between the Ethernet patch panel and the secondary Modbus devices.</note>
         <fig expanse="page" class="- topic/fig ">
            <image href="../Images/Modbus-Wiring_Slave_0000412334.svg"
                   align="right"
                   placement="inline"
                   class="- topic/image "/>
         </fig>
      </div>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">The RJ45 connector <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(D)</b> on the Ethernet patch panel
connects with a RJ45 cable to the RJ45 port <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(E)</b> on the LUFP7
gateway.<note type="important" class="- topic/note ">Do not change the pin-out on the RJ45
connectors/cable.</note>
            <note class="- topic/note ">The correct port <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(E)</b> on the LUFP7
gateway must be used for the RJ45 connection.</note>
         </p>
